        "article_heading_VY7VVQ": {
          "type": "article_heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "You switched to natural skincare, and you even cleaned up your diet. Now, what about your cleaning cupboard?"
          }
        },
        "article_content_aReEFz": {
          "type": "article_content",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The movement towards sustainable living is heating up. From toxin-free beauty to planet-friendly produce, the choices we’re making at home are becoming increasingly more sophisticated. </p><p>We sip on oat milk lattes (soy if we must), dabble in mindfulness, and energetically reject anything that dares to contain parabens. Being an early adopter is hard work, but someone’s got to do it, right? </p><p>But open up the average cupboard under the sink, and chances are, it’s a very different story. The truth is, most of us don’t think twice about the chemical cocktails lurking in our homes. We spend thousands on everything from organic produce to planet-friendly cosmetics, but often continue to choose harsh cleaning sprays we throw into the trolley at the supermarket. </p>",
            "content_class": "",
            "content_text-color": "#616161"
          }
        },
        "article_quote_pVf9TD": {
          "type": "article_quote",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "“One natural cleaning spray<span style=\"display: block\">that does it all”</span>",
            "quote-mobile": "“One natural cleaning spray that does it all”"
          }
        },
