        "article_content_WtDgVY": {
          "type": "article_content",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Packed with pure essential oils from aromatic lemons from the sun-drenched tip of Italy’s toe, Calabrian Lemon is a far cry from the synthetic citrus scents that flood the market. “It’s inspired by the scent we think of when we recall a lovely deep clean by our parents. It’s the classic smell of clean on a sunny Sunday morning.” </p><p>Calabrian Lemon Counter Clean exemplifies the brand's careful and considered approach to scent. Purdy & Figg’s team of perfumers find the purest essential oils from the best raw ingredients, scouring farms and groves at home and abroad for the most aromatic botanicals they can find.</p><p>Take their citrus, for example, sourced from the Cilione family, seventh-generation growers in Reggio Calabria, where the sun, sea breeze and rich soil create what many consider the world’s finest lemons.</p><p>Scent may be the kryptonite for Purdy & Figg’s members, but it’s the powerful natural formula that keeps them coming back for more. “We keep Counter Clean and our members’ homes completely toxin-free by using the best of what Mother Nature has to offer,” says Charlotte.</p>",
            "content_class": "",
            "content_text-color": "#616161"
          }
        },
